BEAUTIFUL DERMATOLOGY

4
00:01:18.369 --> 00:01:19.245
Hello.

5
00:01:20.371 --> 00:01:21.247
Hello.

6
00:01:26.169 --> 00:01:27.670
BEAUTIFUL DERMATOLOGY
DIRECTOR

7
00:01:30.757 --> 00:01:31.800
What are you doing?

8
00:01:33.843 --> 00:01:36.304
-Good morning.
-At this rate, you might put it on me.

9
00:01:36.971 --> 00:01:39.557
Coats these days look so refined.

10
00:01:39.641 --> 00:01:41.559
-What color is this?
-Give that to me. I'll wear it myself.

11
00:01:41.643 --> 00:01:43.895
Goodness, I'll put it on for you.

12
00:01:43.978 --> 00:01:45.563
Gosh, jeez.

13
00:01:45.647 --> 00:01:49.150
Filming finished late,
so I barely made it here on time.

14
00:01:49.234 --> 00:01:50.735
Gosh, you're so cool.

15
00:01:50.819 --> 00:01:53.988
You go to broadcasting stations
and get filmed.

16
00:01:54.072 --> 00:01:55.365
Why are you all dressed up?

17
00:01:55.448 --> 00:01:57.909
Are you going on a blind date
or something?

18
00:01:57.992 --> 00:02:00.662
I use days like this
as an excuse to dress up.

19
00:02:00.745 --> 00:02:02.163
How do you like it? It's brand new.

20
00:02:03.081 --> 00:02:05.125
Regardless, the face is
what completes a look.

21
00:02:05.208 --> 00:02:07.085
What happened to your face?

22
00:02:08.378 --> 00:02:11.172
What do you mean?
I really worked hard on my makeup today.

23
00:02:11.256 --> 00:02:12.590
Let's go. Let's drink coffee.

24
00:02:12.674 --> 00:02:14.592
Jeez, that cold-hearted woman.

25
00:02:15.343 --> 00:02:16.803
I look pretty.

26
00:02:18.721 --> 00:02:20.181
Gosh.

27
00:02:20.265 --> 00:02:24.227
My friend, I keep telling you to come
to get treatments before it gets worse.

28
00:02:24.310 --> 00:02:25.395
Why won't you listen?

29
00:02:25.478 --> 00:02:27.856
It doesn't look good
to get free treatments for being a friend.

30
00:02:27.939 --> 00:02:30.150
Then you can just pay for it.

31
00:02:30.233 --> 00:02:32.652
Your mother-in-law is over 70,

32
00:02:32.735 --> 00:02:35.238
and she comes here
more often than to the grocery store.

33
00:02:35.905 --> 00:02:39.200
Hey, my mother-in-law
has always lived that kind of lifestyle.

34
00:02:40.201 --> 00:02:41.786
Hey, do I look that awful?

35
00:02:41.870 --> 00:02:43.997
Yes. Are you not eating well?

36
00:02:44.080 --> 00:02:46.875
I mean, your face seems yellowish.

37
00:02:46.958 --> 00:02:49.752
-What?
-And your eyes look a little jaundiced.

38
00:02:49.836 --> 00:02:51.004
What?

39
00:02:53.423 --> 00:02:54.841
I'm just tired.

40
00:02:54.924 --> 00:02:56.968
I haven't been feeling well
the past few days.

41
00:02:57.051 --> 00:02:58.094
Jeez.

42
00:02:59.012 --> 00:03:02.140
Hey, that's that.
Do you have any good news these days?

43
00:03:02.223 --> 00:03:04.392
-What good news?
-You have everything

44
00:03:04.475 --> 00:03:05.518
but marriage.

45
00:03:05.602 --> 00:03:08.271
Marriage, my foot. That's so ridiculous.

46
00:03:08.354 --> 00:03:11.357
-Stop trying to be funny.
-You'll be a virgin forever at this rate.

47
00:03:12.525 --> 00:03:15.695
Honestly, on that subject,
aren't you purer than me?

48
00:03:15.778 --> 00:03:16.905
It's been over ten years

49
00:03:16.988 --> 00:03:19.949
since you and your husband
started sleeping in separate rooms.

50
00:03:20.033 --> 00:03:22.744
Doesn't that practically make you
a born-again virgin?

51
00:03:23.494 --> 00:03:24.621
You little…

52
00:03:25.413 --> 00:03:27.832
Listen, the love between a married couple

53
00:03:27.916 --> 00:03:31.336
isn't always maintained
through physical aspects.

54
00:03:31.419 --> 00:03:33.671
It's a world of complexities
and subtleties

55
00:03:33.755 --> 00:03:36.049
that a spinster like you
wouldn't know about.

56
00:03:36.132 --> 00:03:38.051
Fine, you can spend the rest of your life

57
00:03:38.134 --> 00:03:41.512
having your heart flutter
at even the sight of your husband.

58
00:03:41.596 --> 00:03:44.098
You'll be like that little girl Candy
from that romantic series.

59
00:03:47.310 --> 00:03:49.395
Hey, let's tackle those freckles first.

60
00:03:49.479 --> 00:03:54.442
You're such a mess.
It's hard to know where to start.

61
00:03:57.028 --> 00:03:59.072
Let's go, Ms. Cha Candy.

62
00:03:59.155 --> 00:04:00.240
Come on.

63
00:04:00.323 --> 00:04:02.867
Most people throw a fit
because they couldn't become a doctor,

64
00:04:02.951 --> 00:04:05.787
so why did you choose
to become a full-time housewife?

65
00:04:05.870 --> 00:04:08.456
Don't you think it's a waste
of your medical license? I'm done.

66
00:04:12.377 --> 00:04:14.003
I don't think it's a waste at all.

67
00:04:14.087 --> 00:04:17.840
While you were diligently looking after
your patients and starting this clinic,

68
00:04:17.924 --> 00:04:20.093
do you think I was just relaxing at home?

69
00:04:20.176 --> 00:04:23.680
I gave birth to two kids and raised them
into proper human beings.

70
00:04:24.264 --> 00:04:26.849
You've worked hard to study medicine

71
00:04:26.933 --> 00:04:29.185
and used it to work
to create a great life for yourself.

72
00:04:29.269 --> 00:04:31.938
But isn't raising
two human beings like I did

73
00:04:32.021 --> 00:04:35.441
future-oriented and a contribution
to the development of this country?

74
00:04:36.734 --> 00:04:37.819
Candy's leaving.

75
00:04:37.902 --> 00:04:38.736
Hey, are you mad?

76
00:04:39.737 --> 00:04:43.074
-I'm fine.
-You are mad. Jeong-suk…

